<img src="images/banner_create.gif" alt="banner_create.gif (17813 bytes)" WIDTH="496" HEIGHT="71"></p>

<p><br>
The druid is a cleric based class with the widest mix of spells in the game...somewhat a
hybrid caster.&nbsp; The druid does not have any experience penalties or bonuses in
comparison with the Cleric or Shaman.&nbsp;</p>

<p>There are 4 races that can be chosen when playing a druid.</p>

<p>Remember that wisdom is the stat defines your mana pool and your fizzle rate.</p>

<p>A half elf has better stats towards combat and other activities...however the
Halfling and wood elf lend themselves to a more casting role.&nbsp; The Halfling
has decent stats
with a horrible charisma and a wood elf will be a pure caster with its inherent poor melee
stats.&nbsp; The majority of the druids that I have seen are wood elves and Halflings,
&nbsp; I am a <strong>wood</strong>-elf now as I just quit playing my <strong>half</strong>-elf
after level 20 due to doing my stats wrong... It is VERY
important to note that you will NOT be melee capable after level 23 or so due to the fact
that MOBs will cream you. </p>

<p>EQDruids Rank of Races:&nbsp; (no flames or opinions on this - this is STAT BASED
OPINION)</p>

<p>We believe the best starting druid will be +25 points wisdom and +5 points agility</p>

<p>Best - Halfling<br>
Close second - Wood Elf<br>
Distant Third - Human<br>
Last Place - Half-Elf</p>

